title: Grateful Dead Live at San Francisco Civic Auditorium on 1987-01-28
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Taped & transferred by Andrew F. 02/2012 - mixing by Kevin Tobin
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Get Back, Peggy-O, Walkin' Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy, My Brother Esau, Bird Song, Jack Straw

Set 2

When Push Comes To Shove, Samson & Delilah-> Black Muddy River-> He's Gone-> Spoonful-> Drums*-> Eyes Of The World-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

*With extra drummer

reviews.review_text:
WOW!!! This sounds fantastic in 5.1.
Beautiful matrix-- Thank you!

Weir'd's True Colours After Roses Bobby States "Oh God, He's Gone Queer On Me." Then Promptly Skewer The Words To It's All Over Now. As Time Goes On On Weir's Ego And Personality Traits Become Painfully Obvious. A Great Matrix, Some Nice Solos By Jerry And Phil Is Rock Steady. They Are Still Struggling With The Lyrics After The Long Layoff And Intermittent Touring Schedule. Great Sound A Little Rough Around The Edges Performance Wise. Should Have Never Humoured Healy With His Soundboard Effect Follies On The Vocals. It Sure Got Old Fast.
